Weather Alert Script
This Python script retrieves current weather data using the OpenWeatherMap API and sends an alert message using Twilio
if the wind speed is above a certain threshold.

Prerequisites
Python 3.x
Twilio account and credentials (API key, account SID, auth token)
OpenWeatherMap API key
Installation
Clone the repository:

bash
Copy code
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/WeatherAlert.git
cd WeatherAlert
Install dependencies:

bash
Copy code
pip install requests twilio
Create a .env file in the project directory and add your environment variables:

dotenv
Copy code
API_KEY=your_openweathermap_api_key
ACCOUNT_SID=your_twilio_account_sid
AUTH_TOKEN=your_twilio_auth_token
Run the script:

bash
Copy code
python main.py
Configuration
Edit the script (main.py) to customize the location (MY_LAT, MY_LNG), OpenWeatherMap API parameters, and the Twilio message content.

Usage
Execute the script to check the current weather conditions and receive a Twilio alert if the wind speed exceeds the specified threshold.

bash
Copy code
python main.py
